<br>
1.  Scouting tool.  I lead the way through a place like Ssra with my eye of zoom bracer hot-keyed.  I scout every room, corner, etc and tell the monk puller what lies ahead.<br>
<br>
Other mages have used the eye of tallon to scout Plane of Hate, check all the mini's spawn points, and see if Magi P'tasa is holding a stick.<br>
<br>
2.  Group replacement.  If you are near anywhere close to a zoneline, you can send an eyeball to zone-in, target the player, invite to group, and CoH the player inside.  I've done this several times and it works so much better than everyone succor out, grab player, and fight back in.<br>
<br>
3.  Getting a target on a mob.  You can hit a mob with something like malosi or cancel magic through walls, but you have to see them first.  Send the eyeball out to get a target, then pull.  Rottgrime was mentioned in this.  I've also used it in Maiden's eye to single pull the vampires out of their little huts without ever going close to them.<br>
<br>
4.  Exploration.  Sometimes it is just fun to zone in and send an eye out to look around.  You know the area is dangerous and going out solo would be a bad idea, but this way you can at least look.  Also, try standing facing a wall, summon eye, see where it pops up.  I found a place in Kael near the EW zoneline where the eye pops in the Arena.  So I could essentially go in, find a CoH mage on arena raid, tell him to drop group for a minute.  Send in my eyeball, invite him to group, have him CoH me to Arena.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
