They give me consent, and I get their corpses out. The only problem is that you have to target another player's corpse to do this and sometimes MOBs get in the way. Solution: Eye of Zomm<br>
<br>
Of course, you have a limited range to work with. You have to be within a certain radius but yes, walls are no obstacle. It is only distance.<br>
<br>
Basically, you can't use the Eye to summon a corpse to where the eye is... you just use the eye to target and attempt a summon from the place you were standing when you made the eye. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ucereberial.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cereberial</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#333333>(8/19/02 8:45:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1478.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Getting replacment...</span><hr size=1> Locked Doors<br>
