<br>
I often farm Castle Mistmoore for one of my smithing ingredients I need.  Mobs aggro on ME first and not my pet thanks to the new pet faction.  So walking into a room full of 6+ spawns isn't always a good idea.<br>
<br>
However, I send in the eyeball while I wait down around the corner, get a target, and hit /pet attack.  Pet goes in first now and kills mobs while I wait outside.<br>
<br>
There are a couple rooms where the mobs are all SK's.  Even a level 60 mage wants to avoid multiple 400 pt harmtouches and 3+ mobs that hit for 50-60 dmg beating on you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
